REMARKS:  Diagnostic horizons and features recognized in this series are:  ochric epipedon - the zone from the surface of the soil to a depth of 18 inches (A, E1, E2, and E3 horizons);
argillic horizon - the zone from approximately 18 to 62 inches or more (Bt1, Bt2, 2Bt3, and 2Bt4 horizons);
udic moisture regime.
National Cooperative Soil Survey
U.S.A.
